   Atos is a global leader in digital transformation with over 110,000
   employees in 73 countries and annual revenue of over € 11 billion.
   European number one in Cloud, Cybersecurity and High-Performance
   Computing, the Group provides end-to-end Orchestrated Hybrid Cloud, Big
   Data, Business Applications and Digital Workplace solutions. The group
   is the Worldwide Information Technology Partner for the Olympic &
   Paralympic Games and operates under the brands Atos, Atos Syntel, and
   Unify. Atos is a SE (Societas Europaea), listed on the CAC40 Paris
   stock index.

   The purpose of Atos is to help design the future of the information
   technology space. Its expertise and services support the development of
   knowledge, education as well as multicultural and pluralistic
   approaches to research that contribute to scientific and technological
   excellence. Across the world, the group enables its customers,
   employees and collaborators, and members of societies at large to live,
   work and develop sustainably and confidently in the information
   technology space.

